🧭 Project Overview

In this project, we provision an Amazon Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) with a custom CIDR block using Terraform. Assigning a CIDR block defines the private IP address range within the VPC, enabling the creation of subnets, launching EC2 instances, 
and building scalable network architectures.

This project introduces one of the most fundamental networking concepts in cloud computing: IP address management.

🎯 Objective
Create an AWS VPC using Terraform
Assign a custom IPv4 CIDR block
Understand CIDR notation and private IP addressing
Learn why network planning is critical in cloud environments

